1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,304
Psalm 45.

2
00:00:02,304 --> 00:00:09,240
My heart is inditing a good matter: I speak of the things which I have made touching the king: my tongue is the pen of

3
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,160
a ready writer.

4
00:00:11,160 --> 00:00:17,736
Thou art fairer than the children of men: grace is poured into thy lips: therefore God hath blessed thee for ever.

5
00:00:17,736 --> 00:00:23,016
Gird thy sword upon thy thigh, O most mighty, with thy glory and thy majesty.

6
00:00:23,016 --> 00:00:29,784
And in thy majesty ride prosperously because of truth and meekness and righteousness; and thy right hand shall teach

7
00:00:29,784 --> 00:00:37,320
thee terrible things. Thine arrows are sharp in the heart of the king’s enemies; whereby the people fall under thee.

8
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:42,960
Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever: the sceptre of thy kingdom is a right sceptre.

9
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:50,328
Thou lovest righteousness, and hatest wickedness: therefore God, thy God, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness

10
00:00:50,328 --> 00:00:52,512
above thy fellows.

11
00:00:52,512 --> 00:01:00,312
All thy garments smell of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia, out of the ivory palaces, whereby they have made thee glad.

12
00:01:00,312 --> 00:01:06,264
Kings’ daughters were among thy honourable women: upon thy right hand did stand the queen in gold of Ophir.

13
00:01:06,264 --> 00:01:14,952
Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline thine ear; forget also thine own people, and thy father’s house; So shall

14
00:01:14,952 --> 00:01:20,232
the king greatly desire thy beauty: for he is thy Lord; and worship thou him.

15
00:01:20,232 --> 00:01:26,232
And the daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift; even the rich among the people shall intreat thy favour.

16
00:01:26,232 --> 00:01:31,152
The king’s daughter is all glorious within: her clothing is of wrought gold.

17
00:01:31,152 --> 00:01:37,800
She shall be brought unto the king in raiment of needlework: the virgins her companions that follow her shall be brought

18
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:44,880
unto thee. With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought: they shall enter into the king’s palace.

19
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:50,328
Instead of thy fathers shall be thy children, whom thou mayest make princes in all the earth.

20
00:01:50,328 --> 00:01:56,736
I will make thy name to be remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise thee for ever and ever.

